5:
Is it just me, or is it kinda lazy that
they're using adventurers to fix the
river dams?
10:
I don't see the problem. If we can
serve to help our fellow man, then it
is work worth doing.
14:
Uh-huh. Right. Dunno what else 
I expected from the all-mighty
Champion. This is exactly why that
Guild lady always gives us these
kinda jobs.
20:
I mean, sure, sometimes it does feel
like we're being taken advantage of,
butâ€”
24:
Wait, you there! The ground isn't
stable up ahead! You shouldn't
proceed any farther wearing heavy
armor like that!
33:
What's with him? His movements
are kinda funny... unnatural even.
38:
That must have been a landslide! 
It came from where that man went!
42:
Talk about brutal... I don't think he's
walking out of this one...
55:
What are you waiting for? Pull me
out. Please.
66:
I owe you my thanks. I am Londahl.
I'm traveling to the Kaleidoscope.
70: Errr... Correct me if I'm wrong, but...
74: Is the armor the one talking?
79:
Yes, I'm the armor this man wears.
How did you notice?
83:
Normal humans don't survive a
landslide. They also don't twist their
heads around like an owl.
85:
Speaking of which... Is the guy
wearing you dead? Did you kill him?
91:
He was my collaborator. He isn't
dead yet... However, he is no longer
able to move on his own.
95:
Your... collaborator? I don't quite
understand.
99:
Given my form, I can't move by
myself. I require a human to wear
me.
101:
In exchange, I can grant my wearer
great power. That is why this man
wanted to be my collaborator.
108:
But this man, Lloyd, became
complacent after becoming strong.
He was struck by an enemy's blade.
His consciousness has been lost
since.
111:
Without a fully aware host, my
capabilities are limited. It's in my
best interest to avoid harming him,
in case you are concerned.
118: Then I trust you have no complaints.
122: Hey, where the hell are you going?
125:
To the Kaleidoscope. I am looking for
my creator.
129:
Lloyd claimed to have found me
there. The various clues I have
gathered point there as well.
134:
Sorry to burst your bubble, 
but I don't think you're going 
to make it into Palpebra like that.
140:
How do I put this delicately... 
You move like a zombie. 
People are gonna figure out 
something's off...
145:
You will probably be classified as a
cryptic artifact or an evil spirit and
be detained.
150: Then... what do you suggest I do?
160:
Huh, never expected you to be the
friendly one.
164:
Better we keep an eye on him than
anyone else. Dunno if I trust his
whole story either...
168:
We're practically experts at
exploring the Kaleidoscope, and you
seem like you can hold your own.
We'll guide you if you fight with us.
172:
I see. A mutually beneficial
agreement. I see no issue with it.
173:
I trust you'll guard this body as well.
Let's go.
179:
First things first, we gotta do
something about that funky walk of
his...
